cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.LO, cs.SY, cs.PL 

This paper deals with verifying the correctness of network forwarding tables, which falls under the category of network protocols and architectures (cs.NI). It also deals with the verification of isolation properties, which can be categorized under computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper uses model checking, which is a technique used in formal methods and logic (cs.LO). The paper also mentions the use of SMT solvers, which can be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with the verification of networks containing middleboxes, which can be categorized under programming languages (cs.PL) as middleboxes often require custom programming to implement their behavior.
